id: pm-9hry
title: "pm close <id> -m 'text' still hard-blocks with close_reason_required: accept --message text as close-reason fallback (like closed pm-7x8d did for --resolution)"
description: "2026-07-04 sandbox audit #3 (fresh npm-pack CJS project): 'pm close <id> -m done' fails with close_reason_required even though the agent supplied a summary via -m. Agents coming from git idiom use -m for the closing message. pm-7x8d already established the never-block precedent by accepting --resolution as the reason. Fix: when require_close_reason is on and no positional/--reason given, fall back to --message text as the close reason (still recorded as history message too); at minimum the error must acknowledge that -m/--message was provided and point to --reason."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: agent-ux,audit-followup,never-block
created_at: "2026-07-04T10:54:16.932Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-04T17:40:31.600Z"
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-mpbb
resolution: "pm close now accepts -m/--message as the close_reason fallback when governance requires a close reason and no explicit reason, duplicate target, or resolution text is supplied"
expected_result: "Agents can close strict-governance items with pm close <id> -m <text> without close_reason_required, while blank messages still fail and stronger close signals keep precedence"
actual_result: "Implemented resolveEffectiveCloseReasonText fallback precedence in close.ts; close-command spec covers CLI -m, programmatic message, blank message rejection, and existing stronger-signal precedence"
